      <section id="id17042950">
        <title>Activity: To use divisibility rules [LO 1.12.1]</title>
        <para id="id15825693"/>
        <para id="id17750572">Now you can test your skill in division and use the new knowledge that you have gained effectively. Let us see how you cope with the following mental calculation test. Write down answers only, as quickly as you can.</para>
        <para id="id6877859"/>
        <para id="id22492893">1.1 72 ÷ 6 = ___________________</para>
        <para id="id7100731">1.2 54 ÷ 9 = ___________________</para>
        <para id="id15587758">1.3 63 ÷ 7 = ___________________</para>
        <para id="id3777559">1.4 48 ÷ ___________________ = 6 </para>
        <para id="id19631241">1.5 35 ÷ ___________________ = 7 </para>
        <para id="id21520634">1.6 108 ÷ ___________________ = 9 </para>
        <para id="id21899114">1.7 ___________________ ÷ 5 = 9 </para>
        <para id="id17004263">1.8 4 500 ÷ ___________________ = 90 </para>
        <para id="id15835240">1.9 45 000 ÷ 50 = ___________________</para>
        <para id="id22661679">1.10 45 000 ÷ ___________________ = 90</para>
        <para id="id22911138">1.11 5 800 ÷ 10 = ___________________</para>
        <para id="id22961568">1.12 8 900 ÷ ___________________ = 89</para>
        <para id="id22433327">1.13 2 420 ÷ 20 = (2 420 ÷ 10) ÷ ___________________</para>
        <para id="id6870760">1.14 A half ´ 25 = ___________________</para>
        <para id="id6094733">1.15 (30 ÷ 5) = (36 ÷ ___________________)</para>
        <para id="id20100247">15</para>
        <para id="id21768086">Fill in: I got ___________________ correct!</para>
